Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.95,0:00:21.91,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1500)}Every epoch dreams its successor.\NJules Michelet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.92,0:00:33.21,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,700)}Producers\NMasao Maruyama Iwao Yamaki
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.42,0:00:38.22,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,700)}Based on the Comic by\NOsamu Tezuka
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.43,0:00:43.27,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,700)}Screenplay by\NKatsuhiro Otomo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.43,0:00:48.23,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,700)}Character Design/Animation Supervisor\NYasuhiro Nakura
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.44,0:00:53.23,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,700)}CG/Art Director\NShuichi Hirata
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.48,0:00:58.32,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,700)}CG Technical Director\NTsuneo Maeda
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.49,0:01:03.28,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,700)}Music\NToshiyuki Honda
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.50,0:01:08.96,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1500)}Directed by\NRintaro
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.84,0:01:16.06,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,At this moment our state extends\Nits reach to the stars!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.26,0:01:19.56,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I tremble at the honour\nof announcing...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.85,0:01:25.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...the culmination of humanity's\Nlong history of intellect and science.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.94,0:01:31.49,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Our power spans the earth.\NNow it will illuminate the stars!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.70,0:01:36.08,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,May it stand forever! Our Ziggurat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:22.10,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Those robots are getting big ideas.\NThey don't know their place!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.60,0:03:26.56,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,But our economy is unthinkable\nwithout robot labour.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.81,0:03:30.61,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but they cause friction\nwith human workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.07,0:03:34.11,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy is developing new weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.32,0:03:39.62,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What Metropolis needs is a leader\Nwho will be a powerful symbol!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.46,0:04:00.01,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Duke Red, with the Ziggurat complete,\Nwill you be entering politics?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:02.05,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.26,0:04:07.81,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as President Boone governs,\nour state is secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.02,0:04:10.52,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Politics has no need of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:14.15,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. President, would you like\nto see Duke Red in politics?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:21.03,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't encourage him! How could I\Ncompete with anyone so popular?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.20,0:04:28.87,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true there are military\nfacilities in the Ziggurat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.17,0:04:31.79,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Would the mayor care to comment?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.75,0:04:37.30,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask Minister of State Skunk about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.51,0:04:39.84,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurray for the Ziggurat!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.01,0:04:42.30,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Long live Metropolis!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.02,0:04:50.06,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Shunsaku,\Nwhat does ''Ziggurat'' mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.31,0:04:52.73,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.98,0:04:57.57,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Hey! Look up there!\N-What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.91,0:05:08.75,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Malduk! It's the Malduks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.84,0:05:24.68,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.57,0:06:27.83,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You said she'd be ready tonight,\nDr. Laughton.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.03,0:06:29.45,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, well....
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.66,0:06:34.83,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the meaning of this?\NI've given you the best facilities...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:36.33,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...money can buy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.54,0:06:40.80,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,If you could wait a little longer,\nI'm almost done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.05,0:06:45.89,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired of hearing that.\NI'll be at your lab tomorrow night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:50.60,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not the kind of place\nyou'd go to!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.81,0:06:53.23,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,And the place is a mess!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.29,0:06:55.52,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.70,0:07:14.54,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-It's me.\N-I hear there was trouble, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.29,0:07:18.54,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. A robot agitator in the plaza.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:21.96,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You were supposed\nto have that under control!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.17,0:07:24.13,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.55,0:07:28.34,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool! I am not your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.59,0:07:33.77,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I merely found you during\nthe last war and took you in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.98,0:07:35.81,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.46,0:08:03.55,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Shunsaku Ban,\Na private investigator from Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:08.84,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a letter of introduction\nto Superintendent Notarlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.23,0:08:18.89,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.10,0:08:23.27,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying this Dr. Laughton...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.48,0:08:26.36,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...is hiding out...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.61,0:08:30.03,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...here in Metropolis?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.95,0:08:43.29,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. This is a reliable tip from\Nan organ smuggler he dealt with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:47.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The International Human Rights\NCommittee and other organizations...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.01,0:08:49.97,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...have warrants for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.18,0:08:54.81,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...for vivisection experiments\nand dealing in human organs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.14,0:08:59.44,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,To which end\nI ask for your cooperation...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:06.07,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...seeing I've never been in this city\Nand I don't know east from west here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.90,0:09:12.11,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to help, but with\Nthe celebrations for the Ziggurat...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.32,0:09:14.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...going on all week...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.41,0:09:20.58,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...it's taking every single person\NI have to keep things under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.08,0:09:23.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.92,0:09:28.34,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I could give you a robot\nif that's okay with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.55,0:09:30.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,A robot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.13,0:09:34.14,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He's very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.40,0:09:38.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not authorized to\narrest people...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.90,0:09:44.11,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...but he can certainly assist you{\i0}\N{\i1}in your investigation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.41,0:09:51.41,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I have to return him\nwith a full tank?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.79,0:09:57.25,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He only needs refueling\nevery five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.72,0:10:06.47,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Soon they won't need us anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.72,0:10:09.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kenichi. How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.06,0:10:14.14,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Model 803-D-RP-DM...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.35,0:10:17.27,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...497-3-C.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.31,0:10:21.28,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, how do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.54,0:10:35.58,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The completion of the Ziggurat...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.79,0:10:39.75,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}... establishes our Metropolis{\i0}\N{\i1}as the world leader...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.96,0:10:43.17,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}... in industry, economics and culture.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.42,0:10:50.18,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thus is born a state that{\i0}\N{\i1}will last a thousand years!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.47,0:10:53.81,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I tremble at the honour{\i0}\n{\i1}of announcing...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.14,0:10:59.44,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}... the culmination of humanity's{\i0}\N{\i1}long history of intellect and science.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.65,0:11:05.36,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our power spans the earth.{\i0}\N{\i1}Now it will illuminate the stars!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.57,0:11:09.70,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}May it stand forever! Our Ziggurat!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.54,0:11:21.42,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, where do we start,\Nuh, 803, uh....
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.13,0:11:27.13,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,D-RP-DM497-3-C.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.30,0:11:31.01,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have an easier name?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.22,0:11:35.98,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We are not allowed human names,\nas it may infringe...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.18,0:11:38.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...upon human rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.44,0:11:47.19,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! As of now, your name is Pero.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.45,0:11:49.49,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a dog's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.70,0:11:55.24,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I used to have a dog\Nnamed Pero. He was a great dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.70,0:12:00.42,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,In my opinion,\na criminal could not hide...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.62,0:12:03.63,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...up here in Metropolis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.84,0:12:07.42,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I have reliable sources\nthat say he's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.67,0:12:12.22,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Laughton would not hide up here.\NHe would go to Zone 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.47,0:12:15.22,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Zone 1 ?\N-Underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.39,0:12:18.27,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You are a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.81,0:12:24.48,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It is simply a calculation\nof probabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.13,0:12:50.30,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Robots are strictly forbidden...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.01,0:12:53.72,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...to operate outside\ntheir assigned area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.93,0:13:00.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That robot was not authorized\Nto operate at surface level.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.40,0:13:13.57,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, but who are those guys?\NThey look like fascists.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.78,0:13:18.95,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The Malduk Party, vigilantes\nwho started as a political group.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.16,0:13:23.50,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Movement between levels is restricted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.71,0:13:28.92,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No one who carries the mark\Nmay pass through this gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.13,0:13:31.42,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,So that robot had the mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.63,0:13:35.18,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Each block has a gate like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.39,0:13:40.81,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,There are, of course, hidden ways\Nand people who work as guides to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.02,0:13:43.52,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn right! The system's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.40,0:13:53.40,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It takes light\nto create shadow, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.74,0:13:57.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,This level is not\nparticularly dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.41,0:14:03.58,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...but there are places in which\Npolice writ does not run. Avoid them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.83,0:14:09.21,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do that.\nWe're not here as tourists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.81,0:15:10.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Duke Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.73,0:15:13.65,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.17,0:15:36.88,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Very good. Isn't she finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.09,0:15:42.72,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Her final-stage energy processor\Nisn't stable yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.89,0:15:46.98,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you using real organs?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.18,0:15:51.06,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear me, no! That's illegal!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.27,0:15:56.11,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Real organs are quicker,\nbut they don't last very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.32,0:15:59.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hers are mechanical. I made them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.53,0:16:04.12,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,She will be my masterpiece!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.08,0:16:09.71,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,When will you finish?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.92,0:16:14.00,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Within the week.\NIf I start her too early...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.21,0:16:19.22,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...she'll build up too much energy,\Ncatch fire and explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.89,0:16:25.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,My Tima....
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.60,0:17:08.89,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not giving you to anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.10,0:17:12.65,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put on the finishing touches...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.85,0:17:16.15,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...and together we will flee!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.83,0:17:36.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.88,0:17:40.34,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Protecting my father is\nmy most important task.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.55,0:17:45.47,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Father? But Duke Red has no children.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.72,0:17:48.47,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,And the child who died was a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.68,0:17:51.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet! I know what you're up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.60,0:17:57.73,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No mad scientist is going\Nto deceive my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.98,0:18:04.03,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,And no mannequin like this\Nwill steal his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.03,0:18:06.45,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.78,0:18:11.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It is at Duke Red's request\Nthat I've made Tima.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.41,0:18:14.71,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima is the super-being\Nwho is to sit...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.12,0:18:18.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...on the Throne of Power\Natop the Ziggurat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.92,0:18:24.72,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You lie! He would never give\Nthe Ziggurat to a robot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.93,0:18:28.85,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps you should ask\NDuke Red about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.18,0:18:35.90,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you destroy the super-being for\Nwhom the one you call Father waits?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:44.45,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No robot will steal my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.37,0:18:53.50,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.05,0:19:06.13,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}O, ye Gods, give me courage...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.34,0:19:11.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and strength to guard{\i0}\N{\i1}my father from machines!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.91,0:20:13.95,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire! Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.19,0:20:47.99,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,A Malduk set that fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.19,0:20:50.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.82,0:20:55.41,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones up there want to kill us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.95,0:21:02.21,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Atlas is right!\NThey think we're nothing but garbage!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.71,0:21:06.71,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,To arms! Now we have to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.96,0:21:11.72,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Please remain calm. Fire-fighting\noperations are commencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.09,0:21:16.51,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone please step back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.76,0:21:18.68,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Robots out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.73,0:21:25.27,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,First you take our jobs,\Nand now you're trying to kill us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.52,0:21:28.23,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no time to be fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.03,0:21:34.70,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What the--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.73,0:22:25.27,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did he set fire\nto that old factory?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.52,0:22:28.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that strange old man was around.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.15,0:22:33.78,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,An old man? This one?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.99,0:22:37.33,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Yes.\N-Thanks a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.00,0:22:50.38,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.01,0:22:56.14,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. Kenichi, go round the back.\NHurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.74,0:23:58.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Come on, Laughton!\N-Notebook....
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.95,0:24:03.66,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That notebook?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.71,0:24:06.58,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Laughton!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.71,0:24:47.46,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Laughton's lab burned down?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.67,0:24:53.38,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I guess he was doing an experiment.{\i0}\N{\i1}The fire just ripped right through it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.59,0:24:58.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}-What happened to him?{\i0}\N{\i1}-His body was found.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.76,0:25:02.60,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever he was doing...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.81,0:25:06.19,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...considering there are warrants\nfor his arrest...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.39,0:25:09.77,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...it must have been\nsomething dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.98,0:25:14.94,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Father?\NWhat did Dr. Laughton mean to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.15,0:25:18.91,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out! Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.18,0:27:05.51,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.02,0:27:20.44,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That was sure some fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.65,0:27:23.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it was just an old factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.41,0:27:27.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Saves the trouble of tearing it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.87,0:27:36.00,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is strange. She was{\i0}\N{\i1}the most advanced robot there is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.21,0:27:38.59,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There should be something left.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.59,0:27:45.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Pero, who's that?\N-Rock of the Malduks.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.26,0:27:49.56,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He's young,\nbut he's one of their main men.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.77,0:27:52.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,They say he does\nDuke Red's dirty work.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.89,0:27:57.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Duke Red?\Nls he connected with the Malduks?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.90,0:28:00.61,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the party founder.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.19,0:28:07.45,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Now there's no official connection,\Nbut he funds their activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.91,0:28:12.66,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a public secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.87,0:28:14.96,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.92,0:28:22.59,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Where does this sewer come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.80,0:28:26.30,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It merges up ahead\Nwith the sewage from Zone 2...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.51,0:28:29.47,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...and goes to\Nthe processing plant in Zone 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.72,0:28:34.77,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,If she's down there, she'll have\Nbeen chopped up with the garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.98,0:28:36.60,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone else, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.06,0:28:40.77,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The criminal always returns\nto the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.23,0:28:44.15,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,An old saying, but a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.36,0:28:47.53,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We should continue searching\nfor Kenichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.01,0:29:09.72,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.93,0:29:11.85,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.10,0:29:17.56,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no. You call yourself "I".
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.44,0:29:21.07,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,"I" am who?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.61,0:29:25.65,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-"I" am....\N-You are I.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.15,0:29:28.57,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.07,0:29:34.16,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You are "I". I am "you" ....\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.66,0:29:36.16,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I am who.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.66,0:29:42.17,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.\NAnd I'm Kenichi. Kenichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.84,0:29:45.42,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Kenichi.\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.55,0:29:50.80,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, it'll all come to you\nafter a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.01,0:29:56.14,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Your name, your family,\Nyour father, your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.35,0:29:59.14,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Family...father....
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.99,0:30:13.87,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, thanks, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.12,0:30:18.58,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I know this is food,\Nbut it's all rotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.87,0:30:20.17,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Food....
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.37,0:30:26.05,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You put it in your mouth\nlike this and eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.26,0:30:31.05,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't eat that!\NIt'll make you sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.34,0:30:34.10,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't eat. Make you sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.52,0:30:46.11,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Attention Control. Cloud cover 1.1.{\i0}\N{\i1}Clear to proceed with experiment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.32,0:30:49.99,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Magnetic bias 3.7.{\i0}\N{\i1}Continuing line adjustment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.20,0:30:53.28,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Commencing cooling. Opening dome.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.49,0:30:56.29,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}40 seconds to radiation.{\i0}\N{\i1}39, 38....{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.49,0:31:01.79,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Motor, cooling, sensor{\i0}\N{\i1}and operating systems, all go.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.04,0:31:04.63,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Control authorization. We are go.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.84,0:31:09.13,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Energy condensers confirmed{\i0}\N{\i1}at Level 3, plus-33.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.34,0:31:10.63,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Roger.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.32,0:31:33.41,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Observation Group to Control.{\i0}\N{\i1}Transmitting footage from city.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.95,0:31:37.58,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Commencing final preparations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.91,0:31:40.75,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Magnetic target: bias 0.25.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.67,0:31:45.63,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Optical target: bias 1.06.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.63,0:31:52.26,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Radiation equipment in position.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.72,0:31:57.60,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll radiate for three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.81,0:32:04.60,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Citizens won't be affected,\Nbut aboveground robots will.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.81,0:32:10.40,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm having everything recorded.\NThe data will be valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.53,0:32:14.15,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Begin at Level 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.36,0:32:16.32,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.83,0:32:28.00,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Commencing radiation!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.14,0:32:47.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Terminate Level-3 radiation{\i0}\N{\i1}at 180 seconds.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.56,0:32:50.48,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Solar constant deviation at minus 24.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.69,0:32:53.28,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Five seconds to Sector R.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.49,0:32:58.28,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}4...3...2...1.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.87,0:33:03.00,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Omotanium fusion!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.20,0:33:07.54,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Omotanium confirmed{\i0}\N{\i1}in Fraunhofer phase.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.75,0:33:12.00,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}35,000...40,000...45,000.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.21,0:33:17.89,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sunspot field density,{\i0}\N{\i1}800 and rising.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.09,0:33:21.26,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ionospheric disturbance.{\i0}\N{\i1}Communications disrupted.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.84,0:34:39.80,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Level-3 radiation terminated.{\i0}\N{\i1}Control disengaged.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.84,0:34:44.18,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Success!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.22,0:34:49.56,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,This will set\nthe whole world on its ear!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.85,0:34:55.23,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You now hold the power\nof the gods themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.65,0:35:03.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,If only Dr. Laughton had finished\Nbuilding our guardian deity....
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.66,0:35:12.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's caused anomalies in sunspots...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.88,0:35:16.38,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and bathed Earth{\i0}\N{\i1}in harmful magnetic radiation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.59,0:35:20.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's an outrage that he would{\i0}\N{\i1}endanger national security...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.88,0:35:22.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...by developing such a thing!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.22,0:35:29.31,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The Malduk robot hunters are\nusing this as an excuse...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.52,0:35:33.90,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...to cry "human rights" and press\Nfor changes in the Robot Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.23,0:35:37.15,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The pro-robot citizens' groups...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.36,0:35:41.15,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...say that's reactionary nonsense.\NThey're organizing protests.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.36,0:35:44.45,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,There's fighting breaking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.62,0:35:48.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our chance, Mr. President!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.41,0:35:53.42,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We could make a case for treason here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.04,0:35:59.51,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Will the military support us?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.71,0:36:05.43,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Some units are under Duke Red's\Ninfluence, but I can handle that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.22,0:36:13.23,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll stir up the public\nwith a few leaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.44,0:36:19.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Once sentiment is against Duke Red,\Nwe'll arrest him for treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.86,0:36:24.49,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Should military action be needed,\nyou have...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.70,0:36:26.37,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...my approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.04,0:36:38.71,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I suspect he was the guy\nwho did in Laughton.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.92,0:36:42.92,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What I don't understand is\Nhow they were connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.13,0:36:47.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what was Laughton\nworking on, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.18,0:36:51.22,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.47,0:36:56.65,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Laughton's already dead.\NI want, at least, to know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.85,0:36:59.94,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,My client deserves that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.00,0:37:22.46,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Where's he going now?\N-Zone 2, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.67,0:37:27.47,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,There's another level below this?\NHow far down does this place go?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.39,0:37:32.72,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Zone 2 is the Metropolis\npower plant area.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.06,0:37:37.44,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Zone 3 below that is\nthe sewage-handling facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.77,0:37:39.52,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The sewage facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.73,0:37:45.61,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, he was looking\nat a drain behind that factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.78,0:37:51.95,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll report back\nand get permission to go below.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.16,0:37:56.87,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll file a missing persons report\non Kenichi too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.25,0:38:01.00,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Hey! You're old for a petty thief!\N-Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.67,0:38:07.17,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,If anyone was wandering\Naround down there...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.38,0:38:10.01,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...they'd notice him right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.18,0:38:14.22,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,How often are you down here?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.47,0:38:18.02,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Twice a week,\nfor maintenance on the robots.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.24,0:38:34.62,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,These are Albert ll types.\NIt's their last check this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.18,0:38:56.06,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Is anyone here?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.65,0:39:08.49,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You never get used to\nthe stink down here, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.24,0:39:13.62,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No human could last a day\nat this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.38,0:39:28.51,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-What is it?\N-Someone's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.71,0:39:30.38,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.38,0:39:37.10,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What are you doing there?!\NThis is a restricted area!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.31,0:39:38.89,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,So she survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.56,0:39:41.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.90,0:39:47.90,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-What are you doing?!\N-It's all right. They're criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.15,0:39:50.40,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,How do we get out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.61,0:39:57.91,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that, please!\NYou'll hit the equipment!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.21,0:40:08.88,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.77,0:40:28.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy's trying to kill us!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.19,0:41:08.73,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Move! Move! Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.77,0:41:12.07,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You piece of junk!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.53,0:41:15.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.69,0:41:49.77,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.96,0:42:16.72,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.10,0:42:31.52,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.53,0:42:41.03,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it.\NFifi can't go through that gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.91,0:42:46.12,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for everything, Fifi.\nWe'll see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.04,0:42:48.54,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.75,0:42:53.17,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.23,0:43:17.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Fifi!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.70,0:43:29.21,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No weapons through here.\NMay I see your I.D.?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.58,0:43:31.71,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Rock of the Malduks!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.29,0:43:38.46,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Demonstrations are forbidden{\i0}\N{\i1}during Celebration Week.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.67,0:43:42.18,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please disperse immediately.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.93,0:43:45.80,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.43,0:43:50.60,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Kenichi!\N-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.85,0:43:54.10,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Pay up!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.16,0:46:15.96,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-They're not here!\N-They have to be! Keep looking!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.70,0:46:52.62,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Look over that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.19,0:47:24.73,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Atlas?\NWe're waiting for your signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.94,0:47:29.53,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Not today. There are Malduks\nall over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.74,0:47:33.87,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Was there a leak?\N-They're the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.03,0:47:39.12,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock's after them. Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.37,0:47:43.88,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He was at that factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.52,0:47:59.85,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?\NWhere did you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.06,0:48:04.10,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kenichi. I'm from Japan.\NMy uncle's a private....
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.31,0:48:11.07,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-A private what?\N-A journalist! I'm his assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.15,0:48:13.99,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is Rock after you?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.24,0:48:18.79,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.\nHe just started shooting at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.99,0:48:22.41,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't trust them. Let's kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.96,0:48:27.25,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool it! We're not a gang.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.46,0:48:30.21,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He says he's a journalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.42,0:48:37.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,If he can tell the world\nabout Metropolis, that helps us!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.97,0:48:44.40,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't waste time on nice uniforms\Nand our pictures in the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.40,0:48:47.94,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The uniform I die in...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.53,0:48:52.57,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...will be the uniform\nof the revolution!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.78,0:49:34.45,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.65,0:49:36.95,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-She looks like an angel!\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.95,0:49:39.87,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,An angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.04,0:49:51.46,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Around here there's two\nor three families to a room.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.59,0:49:55.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,There are no schools\nand hardly any jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.01,0:50:01.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,They survive on food handouts,\Nbut with the Ziggurat celebrations...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.60,0:50:03.52,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...that's all been stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.73,0:50:08.23,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What does "Ziggurat" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.36,0:50:12.61,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an ancient Babylonian tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.82,0:50:18.07,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The Tower of Babel was one.\NYou know what happened to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.32,0:50:22.49,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The king's pride brought down\Nthe wrath of God on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.83,0:50:28.46,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,History repeats itself.\NThe same thing will happen to Duke Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.67,0:50:33.05,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,But it won't be God this time.\nIt'll be us.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.53,0:51:00.57,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.66,0:51:11.63,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's fine.\nI was just thinking your hair's grown.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.46,0:51:16.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of hair do you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.97,0:51:20.59,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yours is fine right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.68,0:51:25.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get back to your writing.\NNext comes....
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.14,0:51:28.18,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Tima.\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.93,0:51:31.19,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima. My name.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.57,0:51:37.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,So you remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.40,0:51:42.70,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great! Now you'll start\Nremembering more and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.12,0:51:47.70,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Kenichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.17,0:51:59.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I forgot.\NI borrowed this from Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.76,0:52:07.52,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.52,0:52:18.61,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,So the army's with us?\nThat helps a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.82,0:52:21.65,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The underground residents\nsupport us...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.86,0:52:26.33,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...but they're not sure\nif we've got the strength to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.53,0:52:31.29,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The Malduks are to move\Nwhen the Ziggurat celebrations end.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.50,0:52:37.29,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We want you to crush them\nand storm the Ziggurat.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.50,0:52:43.97,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The president will announce\Nthe arrest of Duke Red for treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.18,0:52:46.80,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He will invoke his powers...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.01,0:52:50.89,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...to take control of\nthe police and military.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.89,0:52:57.02,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Metropolis will be governed\nby the rule of law.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.57,0:53:03.03,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,And we will participate as\na proper political party.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.83,0:53:14.54,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, Atlas. The president\Nwill welcome you with open arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.67,0:53:18.29,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The things I get myself into!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.50,0:53:21.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally find that kid\nand look what happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.96,0:53:26.26,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I could not have been\nof more assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.47,0:53:28.55,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.76,0:53:33.68,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been lots of help!\NI don't know east from west here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.89,0:53:38.56,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about Kenichi.\NHe's tougher than he--
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.98,0:53:44.49,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut that out!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.03,0:53:53.04,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look at this, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.83,0:54:39.79,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,"Watch out. Hide, robots.\NCoup d'état."
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.00,0:54:43.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! A coup d'état?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.45,0:55:13.53,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.31,0:55:37.43,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a good look, Kenichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.64,0:55:41.52,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the whole world how angry we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.46,0:56:03.17,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all out of breath!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.13,0:56:13.84,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better get out of here, Pero.\NWe can't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.09,0:56:16.81,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask headquarters for backup.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.97,0:56:20.31,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not leaving you here!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.56,0:56:25.94,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It's robots they're going\nto attack first!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.15,0:56:29.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-I will be fine.\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.36,0:56:36.53,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It is also my duty to ensure the\Nsafety of all visitors to our city.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.74,0:56:43.08,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Just don't stir\nanything up till I get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.06,0:57:02.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to hold this gate\nall by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.56,0:57:08.02,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Demonstrations are forbidden during\NCelebration Week. Please disperse.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.27,0:57:11.57,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, we can't do that.\NOur time has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.82,0:57:17.07,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Why must humanity settle matters\Nby resorting to violence?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.37,0:57:23.87,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we all know that.\NI agree it is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.08,0:57:28.00,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It's our emotions.\NThey vibrate, and all we can do...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.21,0:57:30.80,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...is move forward\nwithin that amplitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.01,0:57:34.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,But without affirming them,\nwe can't survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.20,0:58:02.08,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for the uprising to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.33,0:58:05.37,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,When should we release a statement?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.21,0:58:09.17,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Things should be clear\nby about 1 p.m...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.42,0:58:12.88,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...so I suggest 3 or 3:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.59,0:58:21.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, minister?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.52,0:58:24.48,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hard to relax, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.68,0:58:29.40,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Mr. President.\NI have an unpleasant duty to perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.28,0:58:36.49,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What the--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.74,0:58:40.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gone over to Duke Red!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.91,0:58:46.37,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I am merely history's agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.29,0:58:54.59,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! We can discuss this!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.06,0:59:48.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.06,0:59:56.65,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do humans just go\nand destroy robots?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.74,1:00:04.99,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.17,1:00:13.33,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The coup d'état has failed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.54,1:00:18.46,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Martial law is in effect,{\i0}\N{\i1}under the command of Duke Red.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.67,1:00:23.59,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Abandon your weapons and surrender.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.84,1:00:27.01,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I repeat,{\i0}\N{\i1}the coup d'état has failed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.22,1:00:32.06,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Martial law is in effect,{\i0}\N{\i1}under the command of Duke Red.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.27,1:00:37.11,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Abandon your weapons and surrender.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.24,1:00:42.66,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.86,1:00:47.03,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.46,1:00:53.37,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.09,1:01:00.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You're safe! That's great!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.97,1:01:05.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Are you all right?\N-This? It's nothing!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.64,1:01:09.43,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.43,1:01:17.90,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Her name's Tima.\NWe escaped from that fire together.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.40,1:01:21.61,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima, this is my uncle.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.70,1:01:24.15,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.75,1:01:38.63,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Atlas!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.25,1:01:45.30,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a trap!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.35,1:01:55.73,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,We meet at last.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.60,1:01:58.44,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.45,1:02:07.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.74,1:02:12.66,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me the girl,\nand you might get back home alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.91,1:02:18.04,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make promises\nyou won't keep, Rock!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.14,1:02:31.72,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play games with me!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.97,1:02:34.27,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima, pick up the gun!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.33,1:03:01.04,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have that back, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.29,1:03:04.96,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give it to him!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.98,1:03:23.94,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You going to shoot?\NI'm human, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.86,1:03:29.78,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.67,1:03:49.97,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's these people\nyou've neglected your duties...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.22,1:03:53.14,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...to go chasing after--
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.23,1:04:08.57,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.20,1:04:11.28,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.07,1:04:16.08,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock! What's going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.24,1:04:23.38,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You told me no one survived\Nthe fire in Dr. Laughton's lab!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.58,1:04:27.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,And how did you know about Tima?\NAnswer me!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.55,1:04:37.18,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.43,1:04:41.94,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the one who must sit\Non the Throne of Power.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.81,1:04:47.48,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No robot must ever rule\Nthe Ziggurat and Metropolis!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.69,1:04:49.44,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.03,1:04:51.70,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Robot?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.91,1:04:58.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you fool me?\NYou're out of line, boy!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.54,1:05:00.50,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Get up!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.13,1:05:16.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I never want to see you again!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.97,1:05:18.22,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.93,1:05:25.90,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-So it was you who hired Laughton!\N-What if I did?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.11,1:05:29.86,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come from Japan\Nto arrest Laughton.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.07,1:05:34.07,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Shunsaku Ban....
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.67,1:05:48.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Get in.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.29,1:05:51.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-And Kenichi?\N-You'll see him later.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.50,1:06:29.42,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to see\nSuperintendent Notarlin.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.63,1:06:34.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been transferred.\NHis successor hasn't been named.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.88,1:06:40.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,There's been a mistake.\NThe Malduks have taken my nephew away.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.97,1:06:44.77,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Handle it through your embassy!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.16,1:07:12.96,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At this moment our state extends{\i0}\N{\i1}its reach to the stars!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.21,1:07:16.92,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I tremble at the honour{\i0}\N{\i1}of announcing...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.17,1:07:23.97,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}... the culmination of humanity's{\i0}\N{\i1}long history of intellect and science.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.90,1:07:34.61,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.44,1:07:36.99,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Make it hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.95,1:07:42.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot whiskey or gin I can do,\Nfor a Japanese detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.41,1:07:45.87,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot whiskey, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.95,1:07:50.79,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Who gives a damn about the Ziggurat?!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.00,1:07:55.25,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,And those Malduks can eat dogshit!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.46,1:07:57.13,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.34,1:08:03.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! That was Rock!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.14,1:08:09.02,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he quit the party.\NWhat's he doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.39,1:08:12.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Thanks.\N-Take care.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.07,1:08:22.78,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.31,1:09:00.74,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,A man earlier tonight asked me\Nto give you this. I said no.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.95,1:09:05.95,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted it kept secret\Nfrom Duke Red, and of course...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.16,1:09:11.75,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...I said I couldn't possibly,\Nbut his name was Kenichi.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.29,1:09:18.30,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,"I can't move at the moment...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.55,1:09:22.26,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...so I can't come to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.47,1:09:26.43,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm leaving the country soon.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.68,1:09:31.18,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to see you again. "{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.16,1:09:47.03,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.84,1:10:05.01,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.26,1:10:08.55,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You will bring her back soon,\nwon't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.76,1:10:12.81,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be in real trouble\nif they ever find out.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.10,1:10:16.85,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. This won't take long.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.65,1:10:23.32,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,This wasn't my idea.\nI have to get back.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.28,1:10:27.36,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You tricked me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.87,1:10:32.95,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,How else could I talk to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.20,1:10:38.33,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Kenichi?\NIf you know, take me to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.34,1:10:44.17,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well, well.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.76,1:10:50.64,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,To talk to you,\nyou'd never guess you were a robot.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.02,1:11:01.77,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Father chose\nhis mad scientist very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.23,1:11:06.90,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-What are you talking about?\N-You being a robot.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.11,1:11:10.53,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true. I'm not a robot.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.08,1:11:14.12,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,So what are you? Human?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.00,1:11:21.13,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,So who's your father? Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.67,1:11:23.59,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,My father...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.21,1:11:26.13,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...is Kenichi.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.19,1:11:48.61,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The super-being?\NA mannequin like you?!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.95,1:11:59.33,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you can't take me{\i0}\N{\i1}to Kenichi, I'm going.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.84,1:12:13.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima's gone?!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.98,1:12:27.61,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch where you're going!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.62,1:13:22.21,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see inside this super-being that\NFather wants so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.24,1:13:57.53,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come on, Laughton!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.78,1:14:00.41,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Notebook.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.41,1:14:04.21,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That notebook?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.70,1:15:31.50,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be alarmed. I taught Rock\Na lesson he won't forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.71,1:15:33.34,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Kenichi?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.55,1:15:38.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for him too.\NI need your help for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.13,1:15:40.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You do?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.59,1:15:44.97,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I think they've got him\nsomewhere in the Ziggurat.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.18,1:15:51.73,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to look for him\Non the Ziggurat's data network.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.94,1:15:54.48,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.75,1:16:18.05,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold out your hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.48,1:17:15.23,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.20,1:17:27.58,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.83,1:17:31.71,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi's in that building!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.91,1:17:35.33,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it! I knew he was there!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.55,1:17:39.84,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What happened to me?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.63,1:17:45.26,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You don't know\nwho you are, do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.47,1:17:47.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.85,1:17:57.36,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll report the instant\nwe find anything, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.61,1:18:00.65,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Duke Red?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.32,1:18:04.36,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Anything?\N-We can track the signal...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.07,1:18:08.37,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...by where it burned out\nthe splitters.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.83,1:18:15.17,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Got it!\N-Where?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.37,1:18:18.84,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Zone 1 , South Block 17.\NThe Hotel Coconut.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.34,1:18:28.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, please!\NAm I human or am I...?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.55,1:18:34.69,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you're different\nfrom normal robots.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.89,1:18:39.90,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm human. Just like Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.11,1:18:43.40,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yes, of course you are!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.28,1:18:48.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anyway, now we've got{\i0}\N{\i1}to rescue Kenichi.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.94,1:19:22.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima! I've been looking for you!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.87,1:19:41.00,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what's going on\Nor I'll charge you with kidnapping!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.50,1:19:47.05,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not your man.\NIt's your son you want to talk to.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.30,1:19:49.05,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.34,1:19:51.85,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what the plan is...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.05,1:19:58.06,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...but I suspect Dr. Laughton\nwas involved in it somehow.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.27,1:20:02.06,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,And I suspect you had him killed...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.69,1:20:05.40,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...to keep her a secret.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.87,1:20:13.08,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Take him away.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.66,1:20:17.45,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.48,1:20:50.40,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a special throne\nmade especially for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.61,1:20:54.58,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,One day from here,\nyou will rule the entire world!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.87,1:20:58.37,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Me? Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.58,1:21:03.75,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That is your destiny.\NI'll show you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.89,1:21:16.14,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.35,1:21:17.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.31,1:21:29.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up, Kenichi!\NIt's me! Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.32,1:21:34.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi. Kenichi?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.82,1:21:37.45,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What have you done to him?!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.66,1:21:43.83,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in no danger. We just had\Nto quiet him down a little.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.08,1:21:47.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi? Kenichi?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.34,1:21:53.80,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll file a protest with my embassy!\NIt'll be an international incident!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.01,1:21:59.77,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? I didn't realize\Nyou were so politically important.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.97,1:22:02.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.69,1:22:09.02,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,But soon every nation in the world\Nwill bow down before Tima.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.28,1:22:13.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Make Kenichi the way he was.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.07,1:22:18.33,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What's one or two young kids, Tima?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.53,1:22:23.12,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the power to rule the world!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.33,1:22:28.38,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What power is that? Am I human?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.71,1:22:33.59,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Or am I one of those poor robots?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.80,1:22:40.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't be silly! You're nothing\Nlike those piles of junk!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.56,1:22:44.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Then am I human, like Kenichi?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.98,1:22:49.98,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?!\NYou're no mere human being...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.19,1:22:55.74,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...ruled by emotion and feeling,\Ntorn between morality and love!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.20,1:23:01.29,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the super-being!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.37,1:23:04.96,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,So then I am a....
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.21,1:23:09.25,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought you\nnew clothes, Miss Tima.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.46,1:23:12.21,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you are a robot...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.46,1:23:16.76,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...but you stand at\nthe pinnacle of all existence!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.10,1:23:27.48,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I have the emotions\nand love that you hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.69,1:23:33.53,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because your full capacities\Nhaven't yet taken form.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.73,1:23:39.28,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,As your abilities evolve, they're\Ntaking the form of emotion and love.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.49,1:23:40.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,In time--
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.03,1:23:47.58,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You will become one with that throne,\Na computer weapon meant on conquest!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.54,1:23:53.55,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Your memories and emotions\nwill all be erased!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.80,1:23:57.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.34,1:24:00.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I fancy myself a detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.85,1:24:10.40,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Come, Miss Tima. You should change.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.19,1:24:15.86,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Father, open your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.32,1:24:22.07,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.78,1:24:25.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth?!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.95,1:24:28.12,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.96,1:24:35.63,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It is you who must sit on that throne.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.21,1:24:40.63,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the leader we must bow to!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.93,1:24:46.89,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.00,1:25:15.67,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.47,1:25:29.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,You're awake?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.88,1:26:01.05,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a humanoid, a machine\nmade to destroy the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.88,1:26:07.26,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Not destroy! Make again!\N-Stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.73,1:26:13.64,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi....
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.54,1:27:16.46,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Who threw that switch?\NIt just started up!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.67,1:27:19.71,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-Cut the power!\N-It won't respond!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.92,1:27:23.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going into the red!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.60,1:27:40.48,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Ponkotz!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.07,1:27:43.15,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that alarm?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.36,1:27:46.99,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The omotanium generator's going wild!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.20,1:27:50.62,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,-What's going on?\N-I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.87,1:28:35.95,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Tima!\NYou'll destroy the Ziggurat!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.12,1:28:42.96,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,This comes of trifling with robots.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.34,1:28:52.14,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Her memory's merging with\Nthe data network. She'll go mad!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.47,1:28:56.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus God destroyed the Tower of Babel.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.56,1:28:58.39,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.31,1:29:02.90,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,No! She's no longer the Tima you knew!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.16,1:29:15.83,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.04,1:29:21.79,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The omotanium generator will explode\Nif we don't shut it down!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.76,1:29:33.80,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The chance of human survival will fall\Nto 30 percent within one hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.01,1:29:37.06,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,My entire worldwide\nnetwork of forces...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.26,1:29:41.56,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...will be completely activated\nwithin 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.52,1:29:48.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Their targets are the world's major{\i0}\N{\i1}cities and 7 586 other facilities.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.90,1:29:53.82,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Estimated time period...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.03,1:29:58.08,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...for eradication of humanity\nby biological warfare:
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.33,1:30:00.83,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,17 hours, 27 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.83,1:30:05.54,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Hear that, Duke Red?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.55,1:30:11.84,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Your super-being says\nshe doesn't need us!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.05,1:30:15.93,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima! Come back!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.64,1:30:20.77,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.45,1:30:34.91,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.93,1:31:00.31,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.14,1:32:23.60,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.58,1:32:54.88,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Doctor, we've lost control{\i0}\N{\i1}of the underground power pl--{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.42,1:32:57.38,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.99,1:33:22.41,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out! You robots are\Nnot supposed to be here!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.95,1:33:30.96,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima! It's me!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.97,1:33:44.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi! It's Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.05,1:34:22.84,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.18,1:34:27.35,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,The likes of you...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.10,1:34:31.02,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...will never kill...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.27,1:34:34.60,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...my father!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.56,1:34:38.19,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.72,1:36:37.52,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.91,1:36:52.70,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.16,1:37:36.20,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima! Grab my hand!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.79,1:37:41.46,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}-I'm Kenichi. Who are you?{\i0}\N{\i1}-Who are you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.67,1:37:46.50,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, no, no. You call yourself "I".{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.75,1:37:48.21,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.76,1:37:51.38,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Grab on!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.05,1:37:54.43,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,I am who?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.02,1:38:05.06,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Tima!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.92,1:39:56.59,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you find this?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.40,1:40:13.07,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Fifi?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.44,1:40:17.24,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Fifi!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.23,1:40:57.74,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.53,1:41:01.70,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.51,1:41:21.05,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.05,1:41:25.64,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,...I think I'd like\nto stay here a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.17,1:42:42.09,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I am who?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.09,1:42:44.18,metropolis,,0000,0000,0000,,
